Full Description: Bag of Ice (BOI), located in Lake City, FL, is a leading-edge manufacturer of ice and purified water vending solutions. Description: Secure Payment System based on Blockchain and Virtual Tokens
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Ledger Tokens Corporation is an IT company working in the area of payment systems and applications based on use of innovative concepts of  virtual tokens and blockchain. Its core product – Ledger Pay System is the platform that supports four types of financial services, all based on use of virtual tokens: (1) donations, (2) payments, (3) personal savings and investments, and (4) loyalty rewards.  Collection, distribution and utilization of donations today is very complicated, expensive and slow process. The main reason for that is many intermediaries in the financial flow between donors and beneficiaries. High fees and overheads, long time delays, lack of information on needs and effects for beneficiaries, and various other obstacles make todays donations more beneficial to the charities and various intermediaries than to beneficiaries themselves.   Ledger Pay solves all these problems using an innovative technology approach – peer-to–peer transactions. The System is based on use of secure financial distributed ledger. All participants in a global, international non-profit financial transactions are registered in the Ledger, thus creating global but integrated community. With this approach and by utilization of ledger services, the system has faster, instantaneous transfers with very cheap rates, as overheads are very low. The system is linked to the ACH and bankcard networks. Another very important and distinctive feature of the System is that it uses, so called, virtual tokens for all its financial transactions. Instead of transferring US $, which have many financial and regulatory restrictions, donors convert their US $ into virtual currency called CRIPTo – Charities, Religious, International, Political Token. Then such tokens are freely exchanged between all parties using personal Ledger Pay Wallets. Combined with several other virtual currency systems (Giftz, SocialCash) the system provides rewards for promotion, support, and volunteer activities. Its ultimate mission is to become global, international, worldwide secure system for payments and other international transactions for all those with and without bank accounts and bank cards. The System is already developed (beta) and needs commercial improvements to become operational. The Company has very experienced management team,  several expert advisers, and the first partners and customers.

TectroLabs was founded in 2012 by Andrian Belinski. Andrian’s interest in electronics began at a very early age, when he soldered his first sound amplifier. In college, he developed an interest in digital electronics and personal computers, particularly those based on 8086 and 80286 microprocessors.
